1
00:00:38,940 --> 00:00:40,470
(All characters, places,
and organizations are fictional.)

2
00:00:40,470 --> 00:00:41,770
(Children were filmed
under production guidelines.)

3
00:01:28,490 --> 00:01:30,320
(Episode 3)

4
00:01:42,700 --> 00:01:43,700
Who...

5
00:01:44,870 --> 00:01:46,970
am I? What's your name?

6
00:01:57,120 --> 00:01:58,320
A mirror.

7
00:02:01,320 --> 00:02:04,220
It hurts...

8
00:02:15,740 --> 00:02:16,740
What are you doing?

9
00:02:22,140 --> 00:02:23,140
You're beautiful.

10
00:02:31,350 --> 00:02:32,590
I'll make sure you never get old.

11
00:02:34,520 --> 00:02:37,360
- You'd hate to get wrinkles?
- Wrinkles of the heart.

12
00:02:39,030 --> 00:02:40,560
I don't care about wrinkles on your face.

13
00:03:28,240 --> 00:03:29,240
Tell me.

14
00:03:30,240 --> 00:03:31,240
Your name.

15
00:03:36,250 --> 00:03:37,750
What am I supposed to say?

16
00:03:41,950 --> 00:03:45,360
It hurts...

17
00:03:46,830 --> 00:03:47,830
Does it hurt?

18
00:03:53,100 --> 00:03:54,500
You...

19
00:03:55,300 --> 00:03:56,600
want to...

20
00:03:57,440 --> 00:03:58,570
die?

21
00:04:04,110 --> 00:04:05,380
Don't cry.

22
00:04:08,980 --> 00:04:10,850
You succeeded,
and that's all that matters.

23
00:04:11,850 --> 00:04:12,850
You did it.

24
00:04:13,920 --> 00:04:15,150
You worked so hard.

25
00:05:01,900 --> 00:05:03,000
Goodbye.

26
00:05:20,820 --> 00:05:21,920
This is how I live.

27
00:05:28,360 --> 00:05:30,060
I should've brought some fruit.

28
00:05:32,230 --> 00:05:34,600
- I have milk.
- How's Momo?

29
00:05:35,900 --> 00:05:37,470
- I don't know.
- You don't know?

30
00:05:40,870 --> 00:05:42,910
I'm sure she's recovering well.

31
00:05:43,510 --> 00:05:45,210
James said he hasn't heard
anything either.

32
00:05:45,650 --> 00:05:46,650
It's weird, isn't it?

33
00:05:46,910 --> 00:05:48,710
- Why don't you text her?
- You think I haven't?

34
00:05:51,120 --> 00:05:52,290
But you can go see her.

35
00:05:52,350 --> 00:05:55,120
What? How can I just show up
when she hasn't asked me to?

36
00:05:55,760 --> 00:05:59,130
- She's at Dr. Shin's getting treated.
- For seven months?

37
00:06:00,530 --> 00:06:02,360
Then just how serious is it?

38
00:06:04,100 --> 00:06:06,600
Was she completely unconscious
at the time of the accident?

39
00:06:08,100 --> 00:06:11,670
No one at her agency is talking.
They just say she's recovering.

40
00:06:13,510 --> 00:06:14,740
Is that why you're here?

41
00:06:18,710 --> 00:06:21,650
If her condition were bad,
Director Shin would've fallen apart.

42
00:06:21,980 --> 00:06:25,690
Ms. Hyun also had a couple of fittings
and seemed perfectly normal.

43
00:06:30,390 --> 00:06:31,390
Are you leaving?

44
00:06:39,270 --> 00:06:40,270
Hey.

45
00:06:42,240 --> 00:06:43,600
Don't you have anything to say to me?

46
00:06:46,410 --> 00:06:47,410
About what?

47
00:06:48,510 --> 00:06:49,510
You don't know?

48
00:06:52,510 --> 00:06:53,910
It's just that...

49
00:06:54,750 --> 00:06:58,420
I was hurt because I felt like
you started pulling away from me.

50
00:06:59,490 --> 00:07:00,650
You were hurt?

51
00:07:00,920 --> 00:07:01,920
Yes.

52
00:08:27,810 --> 00:08:31,110
For dinner, I want French Toast
and a Caprese Salad.

53
00:08:32,780 --> 00:08:33,780
Okay?

54
00:08:36,680 --> 00:08:39,490
Caprese Salad.

55
00:08:40,150 --> 00:08:42,090
French Toast.

56
00:08:55,630 --> 00:08:57,540
Get lost...

57
00:09:00,270 --> 00:09:01,270
Get lost.

58
00:09:06,080 --> 00:09:07,280
Get lost.

59
00:09:10,450 --> 00:09:12,990
Is Director Shin still coming
on Wednesday as planned?

60
00:09:40,510 --> 00:09:42,050
There are barely any wrinkles.

61
00:09:42,950 --> 00:09:44,280
I'll look great as long as I dress well.

62
00:09:47,320 --> 00:09:48,320
There.

63
00:09:55,590 --> 00:09:57,030
No.

64
00:10:00,930 --> 00:10:03,840
Excellent. Even I have to admit, I look...

65
00:10:04,200 --> 00:10:06,540
mid-thirties?

66
00:10:08,210 --> 00:10:10,080
When is your birthday, Mr. Ha?

67
00:10:10,480 --> 00:10:13,210
I asked Manager Yoon,
but she wouldn't tell me.

68
00:10:13,380 --> 00:10:16,920
I don't take cakes from my employees.
That's too much sugar.

69
00:10:16,980 --> 00:10:19,120
But still, for us...

70
00:10:22,690 --> 00:10:24,260
Jin Ju, do you drink?

71
00:10:24,690 --> 00:10:25,890
A little.

72
00:10:27,190 --> 00:10:28,690
Should we do the wine pairing?
It's been a while.

73
00:10:30,230 --> 00:10:32,700
Natasha's airport look was great today.

74
00:10:33,270 --> 00:10:34,970
I learned from the best.

75
00:10:35,230 --> 00:10:38,500
I can't take all the credit.
You have to have a natural gift for it.

76
00:10:39,570 --> 00:10:42,910
Should I call you Mr. Ha?
Or do you prefer "Sir?"

77
00:10:42,980 --> 00:10:44,340
Call me whatever you want.

78
00:10:45,040 --> 00:10:48,280
To be honest,
neither of those really suit you.

79
00:10:48,650 --> 00:10:50,750
Then what, you want to call me honey?

80
00:10:51,150 --> 00:10:53,790
- You're like a celebrity.
- I'll take that as a compliment.

81
00:10:53,990 --> 00:10:55,990
Of course. I mean it.

82
00:10:59,460 --> 00:11:01,130
This is so delicious.

83
00:11:04,230 --> 00:11:06,130
This is so delicious, Yong Joong.

84
00:11:10,740 --> 00:11:12,270
They have good pairings here.

85
00:11:12,970 --> 00:11:15,170
Is that birthday on your ID your real one?

86
00:11:18,580 --> 00:11:19,580
You don't know?

87
00:11:22,280 --> 00:11:23,280
No.

88
00:11:23,750 --> 00:11:26,350
- What about Reporter Geum Ba Ra?
- It's the same for Ba Ra.

89
00:11:27,190 --> 00:11:29,520
We even entered the orphanage
on the same day.

90
00:11:31,520 --> 00:11:32,530
Really?

91
00:11:33,690 --> 00:11:35,860
You'll just have to find
yourselves good husbands.

92
00:11:37,260 --> 00:11:40,270
- You think that's possible?
- Where there's a will, there's a way.

93
00:11:40,830 --> 00:11:43,400
They say the deity grants at least one
of your most earnest wishes.

94
00:11:43,770 --> 00:11:45,770
Then why are you still single?

95
00:11:46,570 --> 00:11:48,070
Because I was too busy
taking care of my young brother.

96
00:11:48,270 --> 00:11:51,710
Mr. Ha Yong Joong.
He's ridiculously handsome.

97
00:11:53,510 --> 00:11:55,710
Though he's not quite as handsome
as Director Shin Ju Shin.

98
00:11:56,020 --> 00:11:57,650
You clearly don't have an eye for men.

99
00:11:58,280 --> 00:12:01,020
Whether it's looks or anything else,
Yong Joong is way better.

100
00:12:01,420 --> 00:12:04,060
To each their own, I guess.

101
00:12:04,960 --> 00:12:09,500
But Mr. Ha didn't get far academically,
did he?

102
00:12:09,900 --> 00:12:13,070
What does a formal education matter?
It's his character that's important.

103
00:12:13,270 --> 00:12:16,640
Besides, Yong Joong is smarter
than people with PhDs.

104
00:12:16,640 --> 00:12:18,240
He reads a lot.

105
00:12:20,040 --> 00:12:21,440
It's so tender.

106
00:12:22,340 --> 00:12:23,510
I'll take you out more often.

107
00:12:25,010 --> 00:12:27,250
Is Reporter Geum Ba Ra seeing anyone?

108
00:12:28,280 --> 00:12:30,420
- I have no idea.
- How could you not know?

109
00:12:30,480 --> 00:12:32,180
You said you're practically sisters.

110
00:12:32,790 --> 00:12:34,420
I get the feeling
she's not interested in marriage.

111
00:12:35,150 --> 00:12:37,160
The ones who say they're not interested
in marriage are always the first to marry.

112
00:12:39,260 --> 00:12:40,830
What's Ba Ra's ideal type?

113
00:12:42,290 --> 00:12:43,860
Are you thinking of
setting her up with someone?

114
00:12:46,570 --> 00:12:48,100
You're not thinking of Mr. Ha, are you?

115
00:12:48,370 --> 00:12:49,870
Of course not.

116
00:12:52,300 --> 00:12:53,870
Get lost.

117
00:12:57,110 --> 00:12:59,010
I can't stand the sight of you.

118
00:13:02,050 --> 00:13:04,250
I said, get lost!

119
00:13:06,390 --> 00:13:08,250
Who the heck are you?

120
00:13:08,920 --> 00:13:11,960
Momo, come on. Let Mommy get some sleep.

121
00:13:13,430 --> 00:13:16,230
You're dead meat.

122
00:13:44,860 --> 00:13:46,160
Coffee, and make it weak.

123
00:13:55,130 --> 00:13:56,200
(Post)

124
00:13:59,200 --> 00:14:00,210
What's this?

125
00:14:00,540 --> 00:14:03,140
She's pretty, right?
I thought she might be your type.

126
00:14:04,140 --> 00:14:05,740
(Post)

127
00:14:06,410 --> 00:14:07,650
Looks like she's had work done.

128
00:14:08,710 --> 00:14:12,890
- Nearly everyone gets work done now.
- But you haven't. You're all natural.

129
00:14:13,920 --> 00:14:16,420
- That's because I'm broke.
- You want some?

130
00:14:17,820 --> 00:14:19,390
No, you're perfect just the way you are.

131
00:14:19,690 --> 00:14:20,890
It's not because
I won't give you the money.

132
00:14:22,830 --> 00:14:25,200
"Perfect..."
Is that the right word for a face?

133
00:14:25,800 --> 00:14:27,570
It's more than just being pretty.

134
00:14:28,500 --> 00:14:29,700
Only in your eyes.

135
00:14:31,700 --> 00:14:32,740
She said she's interested in me?

136
00:14:34,670 --> 00:14:38,740
- Yes.
- A PhD likes a middle school dropout?

137
00:14:40,450 --> 00:14:42,410
A high school dropout, to be exact.

138
00:14:42,780 --> 00:14:45,250
- Just meet her once.
- Do you think we'd be a good match?

139
00:14:46,250 --> 00:14:47,250
Yes.

140
00:14:48,350 --> 00:14:50,860
Personality-wise? Our backgrounds?

141
00:14:52,090 --> 00:14:54,890
- She asked me to set you two up.
- I was just asking.

142
00:14:54,960 --> 00:14:56,300
No, you weren't.

143
00:14:57,530 --> 00:14:58,800
You're going to get married, right?

144
00:14:59,470 --> 00:15:01,330
Yes, of course I am.

145
00:15:04,570 --> 00:15:06,870
She comes from a good family,
and she has a great personality.

146
00:15:07,270 --> 00:15:08,940
Plus, she has that foxy look guys go for.

147
00:15:11,610 --> 00:15:12,980
What kind of look do you have, Ba Ra?

148
00:15:18,120 --> 00:15:19,920
I'm clueless
when it comes to women's looks.

149
00:15:21,550 --> 00:15:23,460
Is gaming all you know about?

150
00:15:24,090 --> 00:15:25,120
Pretty much.

151
00:15:28,390 --> 00:15:31,660
Of all the men I know,
aside from our Advisor,

152
00:15:31,730 --> 00:15:33,630
no one is as savvy as you.

153
00:15:33,630 --> 00:15:36,570
You're filled with mature knowledge.

154
00:15:37,770 --> 00:15:39,340
I'll take that as the highest compliment.

155
00:15:39,710 --> 00:15:40,740
It's true.

156
00:15:41,840 --> 00:15:43,240
So when knowledge matures,

157
00:15:43,780 --> 00:15:44,810
does it become wisdom?

158
00:15:47,280 --> 00:15:51,180
You may be half-joking with me,
but I only ever mean what I say.

159
00:15:51,550 --> 00:15:53,090
I don't joke around with just anyone.

160
00:15:57,420 --> 00:15:59,760
How about the Sky Hotel Lounge?

161
00:16:02,630 --> 00:16:03,630
Forget it.

162
00:16:06,470 --> 00:16:08,800
Is the Sky Hotel Lounge okay?

163
00:16:11,840 --> 00:16:13,470
So, is she ready to get married
as early as next month?

164
00:16:16,810 --> 00:16:18,210
That's up to you.

165
00:16:21,110 --> 00:16:22,510
How many cups of coffee
is that for you today?

166
00:16:23,720 --> 00:16:24,720
Four?

167
00:16:24,980 --> 00:16:25,980
That's enough.

168
00:16:27,350 --> 00:16:30,760
Drink something healthy and nutritious.
At least when you're with me.

169
00:16:32,420 --> 00:16:34,160
If this goes well, how about some Chalet?

170
00:16:35,090 --> 00:16:36,230
Is "Eruchal" the thing these days?

171
00:16:36,830 --> 00:16:38,930
I'll deck you out from head to toe.

172
00:16:39,460 --> 00:16:42,700
Clothes by Chalet, shoes by Rugati,
a bag by Evua.

173
00:16:45,500 --> 00:16:46,740
Or an all-Chalet look?

174
00:16:47,270 --> 00:16:48,970
I don't want you to call me
anything different.

175
00:16:50,710 --> 00:16:52,110
Even when we get older,

176
00:16:52,540 --> 00:16:54,280
can't you just keep calling me
what you always have?

177
00:16:55,310 --> 00:16:56,980
I'll take that over all
the designer gifts.

178
00:16:59,150 --> 00:17:00,290
A long time ago,

179
00:17:01,620 --> 00:17:03,320
the first time we met,
in front of the supermarket.

180
00:17:04,420 --> 00:17:05,420
You mean, "Hey, kiddo?"

181
00:17:10,860 --> 00:17:12,460
You're the only person...

182
00:17:14,300 --> 00:17:15,900
who called me that way,

183
00:17:16,600 --> 00:17:17,670
as far as I can remember.

184
00:17:34,250 --> 00:17:35,290
Yong Joong.

185
00:17:39,390 --> 00:17:40,430
We...

186
00:17:41,260 --> 00:17:42,760
seem to really click.

187
00:17:45,360 --> 00:17:46,470
Am I sexy, too?

188
00:17:50,370 --> 00:17:52,370
Turns out, honesty can be sexy.

189
00:17:55,670 --> 00:17:57,210
And you are being
seriously sexy right now.

190
00:18:00,080 --> 00:18:01,210
(James)

191
00:18:05,220 --> 00:18:07,020
- Hey, James.
- Are you out?

192
00:18:07,090 --> 00:18:09,790
Yeah, at a local café with Ba Ra.
You're on speakerphone.

193
00:18:10,390 --> 00:18:11,590
Hey, Reporter Geum.

194
00:18:12,620 --> 00:18:15,830
- Hello.
- So what did my brother get you?

195
00:18:16,160 --> 00:18:17,400
What did he buy you?

196
00:18:17,500 --> 00:18:21,770
Not even a teddy bear this time.
He just said Korean stuff is better.

197
00:18:21,930 --> 00:18:26,270
- I'll get her a bag tomorrow. I'm broke.
- Make sure you get it.

198
00:18:26,940 --> 00:18:30,010
By the way, Reporter Geum,
have you spoken with Momo recently?

199
00:18:30,640 --> 00:18:34,150
- No.
- Is it possible she hasn't woken up yet?

200
00:18:34,410 --> 00:18:36,680
- Why?
- You didn't hear from Reporter Geum?

201
00:18:37,120 --> 00:18:41,320
Momo supposedly passed out scuba diving,
but now she's completely off the radar.

202
00:19:15,390 --> 00:19:16,390
You startled me.

203
00:19:24,030 --> 00:19:26,770
- Are you on a diet?
- I ate way too much yesterday.

204
00:19:32,240 --> 00:19:33,270
It's weird saying this, but...

205
00:19:34,040 --> 00:19:38,010
- Go on.
- I think you would've made a great woman.

206
00:19:38,780 --> 00:19:41,810
- A compliment on my cooking or an insult?
- A compliment.

207
00:19:42,310 --> 00:19:44,050
But there are way too many side dishes.

208
00:19:47,190 --> 00:19:49,190
I don't eat like this when I'm by myself.

209
00:19:49,250 --> 00:19:52,220
You're really getting old.
You used to stuff your face late at night,

210
00:19:52,290 --> 00:19:55,230
and still grill meat at dawn.
Now that you're pushing 50...

211
00:19:58,330 --> 00:20:01,470
I'm a light sleeper.
Why didn't I hear your car pull up?

212
00:20:01,630 --> 00:20:04,270
Because you're old.
Your hearing is the next thing to go.

213
00:20:04,340 --> 00:20:07,440
- Your eyes are already going, too.
- You think you'll stay young forever?

214
00:20:07,540 --> 00:20:10,140
- No.
- You're really asking for it.

215
00:20:10,780 --> 00:20:12,710
I took a cab because I drank.

216
00:20:17,950 --> 00:20:19,720
Is something wrong at the company?

217
00:20:22,990 --> 00:20:24,420
Maybe something's wrong with Momo.

218
00:20:25,590 --> 00:20:27,260
Is that what's bothering you?

219
00:20:28,460 --> 00:20:30,200
Yesterday,
I just felt like having a drink.

220
00:20:31,460 --> 00:20:36,270
Forget Momo and focus on your own life.
I'm dying to hold a niece or nephew.

221
00:20:36,970 --> 00:20:38,300
That's my wish, too.

222
00:20:39,500 --> 00:20:41,270
Is it that hard for you to move on?

223
00:20:41,810 --> 00:20:42,970
Why wouldn't I be able to?

224
00:20:45,010 --> 00:20:46,780
It's just that I'm concerned, that's all.

225
00:20:47,410 --> 00:20:50,350
Why would you be concerned?
She's your best friend's fiancee.

226
00:20:50,650 --> 00:20:52,220
I wouldn't be
if they were happily married.

227
00:20:53,020 --> 00:20:54,620
You think I've only known Ju Shin
for two years?

228
00:20:57,390 --> 00:20:59,090
And it feels like he's hiding something.

229
00:21:02,460 --> 00:21:05,000
I looked into it,
and her decompression sickness is severe.

230
00:21:05,160 --> 00:21:07,400
You can bet Director Shin is taking
the best possible care of her.

231
00:21:09,170 --> 00:21:11,340
Here, take a container of this kimchi
to Ba Ra.

232
00:21:11,800 --> 00:21:12,940
I don't know her address.

233
00:21:14,370 --> 00:21:15,640
You don't know her address?

234
00:21:34,260 --> 00:21:35,960
Burn it. I'm not taking it.

235
00:21:41,470 --> 00:21:43,500
(Nua General Hospital)

236
00:22:05,320 --> 00:22:07,660
Momo, get a grip.

237
00:22:08,260 --> 00:22:09,460
Walk like you're okay.

238
00:22:23,840 --> 00:22:24,910
(Republic of Korea passport)

239
00:22:42,890 --> 00:22:44,700
Director Shin, you know Geum Ba Ra, right?

240
00:22:45,600 --> 00:22:46,670
Yes.

241
00:22:46,770 --> 00:22:49,770
I think Ba Ra is digging around
for information on Momo.

242
00:22:49,900 --> 00:22:51,970
It looks like she even met with
the scuba instructor.

243
00:22:55,270 --> 00:22:58,640
I'm not writing an article, I promise.
You know me better than that, Manager Oh.

244
00:22:58,940 --> 00:23:00,950
CEO Hyun said she's doing perfectly fine.

245
00:23:01,150 --> 00:23:02,510
Have you seen her since the accident?

246
00:23:03,080 --> 00:23:04,750
- I haven't.
- Does that make sense?

247
00:23:04,820 --> 00:23:06,690
She told me not to worry, so...

248
00:23:08,220 --> 00:23:11,220
- If you meet with CEO Hyun...
- I've already texted her,

249
00:23:12,060 --> 00:23:13,190
but I got no reply.

250
00:23:22,470 --> 00:23:23,470
So?

251
00:23:26,300 --> 00:23:30,510
I just thought you should know
since it's about Momo.

252
00:23:36,920 --> 00:23:39,990
Doesn't it seem strange to you too?
With your reporter's intuition.

253
00:23:46,320 --> 00:23:47,330
Like you say,

254
00:23:48,790 --> 00:23:50,430
what if Momo is in some kind of...

255
00:23:51,400 --> 00:23:53,000
worst-case scenario,

256
00:23:55,470 --> 00:23:56,700
what are you going to do then?

257
00:24:01,310 --> 00:24:02,440
When it comes to the heart...

258
00:24:05,010 --> 00:24:06,810
Shin Ju Shin has a cold side.

259
00:24:07,380 --> 00:24:09,010
To put it nicely, he's just rational.

260
00:24:10,650 --> 00:24:12,020
And it's not like they're married.

261
00:24:13,650 --> 00:24:16,190
In that situation, I wonder how long
he can keep looking after her.

262
00:24:17,590 --> 00:24:20,490
He's bound to get worn out.
And it's not like he has a low-stress job.

263
00:24:23,030 --> 00:24:24,400
And you wouldn't get worn out?

264
00:24:32,170 --> 00:24:33,410
Slow down.

265
00:24:43,350 --> 00:24:44,820
You've never really been in love,
have you?

266
00:24:47,990 --> 00:24:49,520
And for you, that's Momo?

267
00:24:54,290 --> 00:24:55,790
What's so great about her, anyway?

268
00:24:57,730 --> 00:24:58,830
Is it because she's a celebrity?

269
00:25:00,270 --> 00:25:02,370
Lee Ye Rim, Hong Mi Jeong,
and Jeong Chun Hee are celebrities, too.

270
00:25:02,530 --> 00:25:04,000
I've met them all at gatherings.

271
00:25:06,670 --> 00:25:07,770
You can't really explain...

272
00:25:09,410 --> 00:25:11,080
a person's feelings, you know?

273
00:25:14,210 --> 00:25:16,650
If the situation is really that serious,

274
00:25:18,120 --> 00:25:20,220
and Director Shin
eventually gives up on her...

275
00:25:23,460 --> 00:25:25,220
are you saying you're going to take
responsibility for her?

276
00:25:27,530 --> 00:25:28,530
For her entire life?

277
00:25:34,730 --> 00:25:36,270
How noble of you.

278
00:25:37,570 --> 00:25:40,070
To Mr. Ha and his undying love.

279
00:25:48,180 --> 00:25:49,780
You're not being yourself today.

280
00:25:50,380 --> 00:25:51,480
You're so cynical.

281
00:25:53,590 --> 00:25:55,050
How well do you even know me?

282
00:25:56,390 --> 00:25:59,090
What is it that I don't know? Tell me.

283
00:26:02,130 --> 00:26:05,660
Other than that I was an abandoned orphan,
you know nothing about me.

284
00:26:06,130 --> 00:26:07,500
You weren't abandoned.

285
00:26:08,400 --> 00:26:10,800
It must have been an impossible situation.
I can tell by looking at you.

286
00:26:11,870 --> 00:26:13,340
I can tell it's in your blood.

287
00:26:14,310 --> 00:26:15,470
You've got good character.

288
00:26:18,240 --> 00:26:19,340
My name...

289
00:26:21,280 --> 00:26:22,380
Who gave you that name?

290
00:26:25,120 --> 00:26:26,580
How would I know?

291
00:26:31,720 --> 00:26:32,960
But I think...

292
00:26:33,560 --> 00:26:34,830
It's just a guess...

293
00:26:38,430 --> 00:26:39,630
I'd rather not say.

294
00:26:46,640 --> 00:26:47,640
Are you mad at me?

295
00:26:50,280 --> 00:26:51,910
I thought you'd understand.

296
00:26:56,280 --> 00:26:59,880
I don't like how you're addressing me.
Don't call me Mr. Ha. It feels impersonal.

297
00:27:00,520 --> 00:27:02,120
It's not like we have that many employees.

298
00:27:03,620 --> 00:27:05,520
You should meet Director Shin,

299
00:27:06,190 --> 00:27:08,630
find a way to see Momo for yourself,

300
00:27:09,460 --> 00:27:11,200
and settle this once and for all.

301
00:27:21,470 --> 00:27:24,380
I have an article to write.
I'll get going.

302
00:27:25,210 --> 00:27:26,210
- Excuse me?
- Yes.

303
00:27:26,280 --> 00:27:27,310
No, go ahead and finish your drink.

304
00:27:39,090 --> 00:27:40,330
(Available)

305
00:29:16,920 --> 00:29:18,060
How's Momo?

306
00:29:20,690 --> 00:29:22,160
I don't want her to see me like this.

307
00:29:25,830 --> 00:29:26,930
She's the same.

308
00:29:33,440 --> 00:29:35,070
Don't let your mind run wild.

309
00:29:35,970 --> 00:29:37,680
I'll wrap this up without any issues.

310
00:29:39,910 --> 00:29:41,050
How are you going to wrap it up?

311
00:29:43,920 --> 00:29:45,920
How did your seminar presentation go?

312
00:29:47,050 --> 00:29:48,050
It was fine.

313
00:29:49,490 --> 00:29:52,390
- I'm sorry. I came empty-handed.
- Don't be silly.

314
00:29:55,330 --> 00:29:56,530
This is all very confusing, isn't it?

315
00:29:57,130 --> 00:29:58,660
You'll get used to it. Eventually.

316
00:30:01,200 --> 00:30:03,300
You should go. You must be tired.

317
00:30:28,830 --> 00:30:30,460
Sometimes when I look in the mirror,

318
00:30:31,160 --> 00:30:34,730
I can't tell if I'm Momo
or if I'm looking at her.

319
00:31:36,360 --> 00:31:41,730
(Yong Joong)

320
00:32:06,860 --> 00:32:07,890
Momo...

321
00:32:11,700 --> 00:32:13,460
How can I live without seeing her?

322
00:32:34,750 --> 00:32:36,350
(Ba Ra)

323
00:32:36,720 --> 00:32:38,260
(Send me your address...)

324
00:32:45,460 --> 00:32:47,170
(Send me your address...)

325
00:32:47,230 --> 00:32:48,230
(Where do you live? Are you asleep?)

326
00:33:10,090 --> 00:33:11,290
(Yong Joong)

327
00:33:11,520 --> 00:33:12,860
Are you still mad, kiddo?

328
00:33:33,540 --> 00:33:34,550
What book is that?

329
00:33:35,150 --> 00:33:37,250
("Mouth Management")

330
00:33:39,750 --> 00:33:40,750
Come on up.

331
00:33:42,250 --> 00:33:46,120
- Is this a bad time?
- I can't eat out. I have surgery later.

332
00:34:00,270 --> 00:34:04,710
We were all in disbelief
when your father passed so suddenly.

333
00:34:04,780 --> 00:34:07,650
- Were you there?
- As the orphanage's representative.

334
00:34:08,580 --> 00:34:10,310
So many people came to pay their respects.

335
00:34:11,680 --> 00:34:15,220
Honestly, my mother's death was harder.
I was just a kid.

336
00:34:16,920 --> 00:34:17,920
Am I making you uncomfortable?

337
00:34:18,560 --> 00:34:21,260
Do you mind if I get this to go?
I usually have late lunch.

338
00:34:21,530 --> 00:34:22,630
This is my first meal of the day.

339
00:34:24,860 --> 00:34:26,560
Are you going around investigating Momo?

340
00:34:27,770 --> 00:34:30,030
- I heard about it.
- From who?

341
00:34:35,640 --> 00:34:38,040
- It's not an investigation. It's...
- For a story?

342
00:34:38,540 --> 00:34:39,640
Or as a concerned friend?

343
00:34:43,550 --> 00:34:45,250
I heard you two were pretty close.

344
00:34:48,720 --> 00:34:52,390
I'm just worried.
I haven't heard from her in so long.

345
00:34:52,690 --> 00:34:55,490
Her phone is still turned off,
and Jin Ju said she had an accident...

346
00:34:55,560 --> 00:34:56,830
It wasn't that serious an accident.

347
00:34:58,200 --> 00:34:59,600
She's out of the country.

348
00:35:00,500 --> 00:35:02,330
She was exhausted,
so I told her to take a break.

349
00:35:04,900 --> 00:35:06,170
She'll be back soon enough.

350
00:35:07,270 --> 00:35:09,010
About me and Momo dating...

351
00:35:10,240 --> 00:35:11,380
Did you hear it from Kim Jin Ju?

352
00:35:13,510 --> 00:35:17,080
I can't reveal my sources.
It wasn't Jin Ju.

353
00:35:17,150 --> 00:35:21,190
We're both too busy to see each other.
We just run into each other at gatherings.

354
00:35:21,250 --> 00:35:22,750
And even that was only once in a while.

355
00:35:22,820 --> 00:35:25,120
You know my father was very proud of you,
don't you?

356
00:35:28,890 --> 00:35:30,260
Running the foundation...

357
00:35:31,060 --> 00:35:32,360
He found it so worthwhile.

358
00:35:35,730 --> 00:35:37,870
If you ever need help with anything,
let me know.

359
00:35:38,540 --> 00:35:40,840
- I don't.
- You never know.

360
00:35:41,470 --> 00:35:42,640
Don't be so sure.

361
00:35:44,640 --> 00:35:47,410
By the way,
I saw you interviewed Ha Yong Joong.

362
00:35:47,850 --> 00:35:49,080
He's been a friend of mine
since we were kids.

363
00:35:50,010 --> 00:35:52,720
He also played the double bass
at the appreciation gala.

364
00:35:52,780 --> 00:35:54,490
Why did you leave so early that night?

365
00:35:55,490 --> 00:35:57,690
I was running a little late
because I had an emergency surgery,

366
00:35:58,860 --> 00:35:59,860
and I saw you were leaving.

367
00:36:00,930 --> 00:36:02,530
I remember because of your ivory coat.

368
00:36:03,360 --> 00:36:05,560
My mother used to wear an ivory coat
a lot.

369
00:36:08,630 --> 00:36:10,470
Please tell Momo I said hi.

370
00:36:15,340 --> 00:36:16,570
I'll take it to go.

371
00:36:21,410 --> 00:36:24,050
Pack it for her to go. The sandwiches.

372
00:36:32,590 --> 00:36:35,590
I can't relay the message.
You should tell her in person.

373
00:36:43,400 --> 00:36:44,400
Hello?

374
00:36:45,300 --> 00:36:47,870
- Yes?
- Where've you been? Haven't you seen it?

375
00:36:47,940 --> 00:36:50,540
- The article on Momo's engagement.
- Where did it run?

376
00:36:51,280 --> 00:36:52,310
Got it.

377
00:36:55,550 --> 00:36:57,580
The inevitable has happened, Momo.

378
00:36:57,950 --> 00:36:59,720
Did you already know about this, sir?

379
00:37:05,120 --> 00:37:06,690
("Exclusive, Momo's Secret Engagement!")

380
00:37:06,690 --> 00:37:07,830
("Fiance is Director Shin Ju Shin
of Nua Medical")

381
00:37:16,030 --> 00:37:18,100
("Exclusive, Momo's Secret Engagement!")

382
00:37:18,100 --> 00:37:19,470
(Two families have met.
Yet, there is no official announcement.)

383
00:37:22,740 --> 00:37:24,380
(Surprised by his handsome looks,
belying his director title...)

384
00:37:24,440 --> 00:37:25,440
(Innocent looks that belie his title...)

385
00:37:25,510 --> 00:37:27,240
(and even more surprised
by his fresh-faced youth)

386
00:37:27,310 --> 00:37:30,510
(We interviewed Director Shin and heard
the full story of their romance.)

387
00:37:34,990 --> 00:37:36,520
- Is this for real?
- We need to publish by eight o'clock.

388
00:37:37,390 --> 00:37:39,560
- Hey, over there.
- This is it.

389
00:37:45,660 --> 00:37:48,000
("Exclusive Interview with Momo's Fiance,
Director Shin Ju Shin")

390
00:37:48,670 --> 00:37:51,370
I just met with Director Shin Ju Shin
and posted the interview.

391
00:37:51,740 --> 00:37:52,740
You interviewed him?

392
00:37:53,040 --> 00:37:54,810
- Yes.
- When?

393
00:37:54,870 --> 00:37:58,380
- I was with him when you called earlier.
- You should've told me then!

394
00:37:58,980 --> 00:37:59,980
I knew you'd pull through.

395
00:38:10,990 --> 00:38:11,990
Yes?

396
00:38:12,720 --> 00:38:14,430
I just met with Director Shin Ju Shin.

397
00:38:15,060 --> 00:38:17,730
He said Momo's fine
and that she's gone abroad to rest.

398
00:38:19,430 --> 00:38:20,430
That's a relief.

399
00:38:23,470 --> 00:38:24,540
Did you see the article?

400
00:38:25,840 --> 00:38:26,840
Yes.

401
00:38:30,210 --> 00:38:33,940
Can you toss me a decent engagement photo?
You must've taken some, right?

402
00:38:34,250 --> 00:38:35,510
A really nice one of the two of them.

403
00:38:37,150 --> 00:38:38,250
Ju Shin would kill me.

404
00:38:38,620 --> 00:38:40,790
His picture's already out there
and the story went viral.

405
00:38:41,620 --> 00:38:43,450
Do you have any idea
how much my boss chewed me out?

406
00:38:43,950 --> 00:38:45,820
All because I was trying to be loyal
and keep it a secret...

407
00:38:48,890 --> 00:38:50,830
I won't reveal my source, of course.

408
00:38:51,330 --> 00:38:53,960
People will just assume
it was leaked by the wedding studio.

409
00:38:54,430 --> 00:38:56,530
- If I can't make up for this...
- All right, fine.

410
00:38:58,570 --> 00:38:59,600
What's with the sudden change of heart?

411
00:39:00,400 --> 00:39:01,740
You've been ignoring
all my calls and texts.

412
00:39:04,780 --> 00:39:05,840
It's not a change of heart.

413
00:39:07,010 --> 00:39:08,010
Then what is it?

414
00:39:09,750 --> 00:39:10,750
I'm sorry.

415
00:39:11,250 --> 00:39:12,580
I'll be more respectful from now on.

416
00:39:15,020 --> 00:39:17,220
- Director Shin Ju Shin!
- Just give us one comment!

417
00:39:17,290 --> 00:39:18,890
- I have an interview with Mr. Shin!
- He has patients to see.

418
00:39:18,960 --> 00:39:21,860
- We're reporting from Momo's house.
- Please just open the door!

419
00:39:21,960 --> 00:39:23,330
- We're from CBS News!
- Come on, please open the door!

420
00:39:23,390 --> 00:39:25,530
- Please, just open the door!
- Just open up!

421
00:39:25,600 --> 00:39:26,600
This will only take a moment!

422
00:39:40,780 --> 00:39:41,780
What are you doing?

423
00:39:43,950 --> 00:39:44,950
Go back inside.

424
00:39:48,550 --> 00:39:49,550
Who am I?

425
00:39:53,190 --> 00:39:54,460
I...

426
00:39:55,890 --> 00:39:58,300
The one you're referring to...
Who is that?

427
00:40:04,440 --> 00:40:05,770
Don't you miss me?

428
00:40:06,970 --> 00:40:08,110
You don't remember me?

429
00:40:11,380 --> 00:40:12,540
I don't know.

430
00:40:17,210 --> 00:40:18,520
Get lost.

431
00:40:19,520 --> 00:40:20,520
You get lost.

432
00:40:23,720 --> 00:40:25,160
You're so dead.

433
00:40:26,020 --> 00:40:27,190
How can you say that to me, your mom?

434
00:40:29,730 --> 00:40:30,860
(Surgery Center)

435
00:40:31,560 --> 00:40:32,560
What am I going to do?

436
00:40:33,100 --> 00:40:35,300
They won't stop ringing the bell,
so I had to turn off the intercom.

437
00:40:35,930 --> 00:40:37,200
For now, there's no other way...

438
00:40:39,140 --> 00:40:40,140
but to endure it.

439
00:40:40,670 --> 00:40:42,840
So we endure it, and then what?

440
00:40:45,410 --> 00:40:46,410
They broke up?

441
00:40:46,680 --> 00:40:47,710
I'll think about it.

442
00:40:50,180 --> 00:40:51,180
Let me think about it.

443
00:40:52,950 --> 00:40:54,020
I guess you have no other choice.

444
00:40:59,560 --> 00:41:00,920
Then just announce it tomorrow.

445
00:41:01,560 --> 00:41:02,690
I won't have any time for a while.

446
00:41:03,890 --> 00:41:05,230
And that'll just stir up
another huge mess.

447
00:41:05,400 --> 00:41:07,560
If you're so busy, why'd you
even do that interview with Sungwoo Daily?

448
00:41:07,930 --> 00:41:08,930
I didn't give them an interview.

449
00:41:09,630 --> 00:41:10,670
She's a reporter, all right.

450
00:41:12,540 --> 00:41:14,310
I heard she was snooping around
like she was onto something.

451
00:41:14,670 --> 00:41:16,010
So I called her in
and gave her the runaround, but...

452
00:41:16,370 --> 00:41:17,410
And that's what she wrote?

453
00:41:17,910 --> 00:41:18,910
Yes.

454
00:41:20,480 --> 00:41:23,310
Hello. We met before
at the exhibit with Momo.

455
00:41:23,850 --> 00:41:25,080
I'm from the culture desk
at Sungwoo Daily.

456
00:41:26,980 --> 00:41:28,690
I could tell she was something else.

457
00:41:29,790 --> 00:41:30,850
(Sungwoo Daily)

458
00:41:32,320 --> 00:41:34,160
(Director Shin Ju Shin)

459
00:41:39,100 --> 00:41:40,430
(Director Shin Ju Shin)

460
00:41:42,030 --> 00:41:43,030
Yes, Director Shin.

461
00:41:43,670 --> 00:41:45,140
Did I have an interview with you today?

462
00:41:47,000 --> 00:41:48,010
I'm sorry.

463
00:41:48,710 --> 00:41:51,540
I'm in the middle of writing the article.
Can I call you back when I'm done?

464
00:41:51,880 --> 00:41:52,880
Another story about us?

465
00:41:53,480 --> 00:41:55,250
Yes, a follow-up piece.

466
00:41:55,850 --> 00:41:56,850
Geum Ba Ra.

467
00:41:57,250 --> 00:41:58,250
Yes, Director Shin.

468
00:41:59,720 --> 00:42:00,880
You're biting the hand that fed you?

469
00:42:02,050 --> 00:42:04,520
And you, of all people,
are going to take it even further?

470
00:42:05,260 --> 00:42:07,490
- After you read the article...
- Don't write anything else.

471
00:42:10,460 --> 00:42:13,360
Rather than let other outlets
write sensationalist garbage,

472
00:42:13,800 --> 00:42:15,700
it's better to release
a well-written story based on the facts...

473
00:42:15,770 --> 00:42:18,700
and help both of your images.
That is my professional opinion.

474
00:42:18,940 --> 00:42:20,100
And who are you to make that call?

475
00:42:21,000 --> 00:42:23,310
An interview that never happened.
That's what's fiction, an outright lie.

476
00:42:23,940 --> 00:42:25,280
I'll make sure you have nothing
to worry about.

477
00:42:25,340 --> 00:42:27,540
Is that what they taught you
at the Nua Orphanage?

478
00:42:28,010 --> 00:42:29,380
I wasn't taught anything there.

479
00:42:29,810 --> 00:42:33,120
You should have a shred of conscience.
You'll stop at nothing...

480
00:42:33,180 --> 00:42:34,790
I'll call you when I'm finished.

481
00:42:36,050 --> 00:42:37,050
Goodbye.

482
00:42:46,230 --> 00:42:47,830
("Rumors of Momo's Broken Engagement,
Couple Not in Contact")

483
00:42:47,900 --> 00:42:49,830
("Momo's Representative on Rumors:
'No Comment,' A Puzzling Response")

484
00:42:49,900 --> 00:42:51,170
("Scoop:
Momo's Fairytale-like Secret Engagement")

485
00:42:52,940 --> 00:42:54,240
("Scoop:
Momo's Fairytale-like Secret Engagement")

486
00:42:54,670 --> 00:42:56,470
("Momo's Fairytale-like
Secret Engagement")

487
00:42:58,640 --> 00:43:00,440
("Momo's Fairytale-like
Secret Engagement")

488
00:43:00,510 --> 00:43:03,950
(Geum Ba Ra)

489
00:43:08,290 --> 00:43:09,290
Hello?

490
00:43:10,520 --> 00:43:11,520
This is Geum Ba Ra.

491
00:43:11,990 --> 00:43:13,690
Because of this exclusive interview
that never happened,

492
00:43:14,860 --> 00:43:16,360
all the other news outlets
are in an uproar.

493
00:43:17,260 --> 00:43:19,860
May I state my opinion?

494
00:43:22,630 --> 00:43:24,740
At the end of the day,
it's true that you two are engaged.

495
00:43:24,800 --> 00:43:26,840
It's a reporter's calling
to report the truth.

496
00:43:28,440 --> 00:43:29,840
I'm asking why you published
a fabricated story.

497
00:43:31,340 --> 00:43:33,580
What did Momo say?

498
00:43:36,050 --> 00:43:37,820
Just answer my question.

499
00:43:38,450 --> 00:43:39,880
As you said,

500
00:43:40,250 --> 00:43:42,790
When the Chairman treated me to dinner
after I got into college,

501
00:43:43,350 --> 00:43:46,760
he told me I was the face
and the pride of Nua Orphanage.

502
00:43:47,390 --> 00:43:49,930
Everyone at my company knows
I grew up in an orphanage,

503
00:43:50,360 --> 00:43:52,730
so I have to work harder than the others
just so they won't dismiss me.

504
00:43:52,800 --> 00:43:54,830
That's how I survive in this business
without getting crushed.

505
00:43:55,470 --> 00:43:56,970
If I succeed and make a name for myself,

506
00:43:57,770 --> 00:44:00,670
you think you'll never need a favor
from me, Director Shin?

507
00:44:01,540 --> 00:44:02,910
You think I don't have connections
in the media?

508
00:44:04,780 --> 00:44:05,810
I've more than I know what to do with.

509
00:44:06,740 --> 00:44:10,410
I'm sure you do.
But I'm not just a typical connection.

510
00:44:11,180 --> 00:44:13,320
When you get down to it,
you could call me family.

511
00:44:13,880 --> 00:44:15,420
Part of the Nua Foundation family.

512
00:44:18,760 --> 00:44:21,860
Please, just think of it
as giving me a leg up.

513
00:44:23,160 --> 00:44:24,630
You have every right to be upset.

514
00:44:26,230 --> 00:44:27,560
And for that, I apologize.

515
00:44:29,370 --> 00:44:32,340
To be honest,
I knew about your engagement for a while.

516
00:44:33,940 --> 00:44:35,070
You heard it from Kim Jin Ju, didn't you?

517
00:44:36,140 --> 00:44:38,840
I'm on the Culture Desk, so I have sources
at the salons that celebrities frequent.

518
00:44:38,910 --> 00:44:41,480
I get all kinds of intel from them.
It's fast and accurate.

519
00:44:45,050 --> 00:44:46,050
I'll let it slide this time.

520
00:44:46,620 --> 00:44:47,850
Don't you dare stab me in the back again.

521
00:44:49,250 --> 00:44:50,250
I promise.

522
00:44:51,920 --> 00:44:53,290
You owe me one.

523
00:44:54,890 --> 00:44:58,400
I wouldn't be where I am today
without the Chairman and you, Director.

524
00:44:59,060 --> 00:45:00,930
I will be sure to repay everything I owe,
including this.

525
00:45:01,400 --> 00:45:03,400
I don't care if you're a reporter
or the head of a media company,

526
00:45:04,570 --> 00:45:05,940
You do not cross the line with me.

527
00:45:07,670 --> 00:45:09,740
Yes. I'm sorry.

528
00:45:10,410 --> 00:45:11,410
You can go now.

529
00:45:11,780 --> 00:45:12,780
Yes, sir.

530
00:45:53,020 --> 00:45:54,450
Is there anything you want to eat?

531
00:45:58,890 --> 00:45:59,960
Who am I?

532
00:46:24,550 --> 00:46:25,850
(To my dearest Momo,)

533
00:46:25,920 --> 00:46:27,150
My dearest Momo.

534
00:46:28,650 --> 00:46:29,720
If it weren't for you,

535
00:46:31,360 --> 00:46:34,390
I would've left this world
a long time ago.

536
00:46:35,930 --> 00:46:37,430
That I have to leave you like this...

537
00:46:49,910 --> 00:46:51,510
this mother who is leaving you now...

538
00:46:52,280 --> 00:46:54,080
I hope you can understand and forgive me.

539
00:46:56,480 --> 00:46:58,280
I could never let you see,

540
00:46:59,350 --> 00:47:00,620
but at some point,

541
00:47:01,350 --> 00:47:05,720
I find it hard to even breathe.

542
00:47:07,920 --> 00:47:09,090
For no reason at all,

543
00:47:10,130 --> 00:47:11,700
every day was filled with despair...

544
00:47:12,460 --> 00:47:13,760
and sorrow.

545
00:47:15,630 --> 00:47:17,330
I tried to hold on a little longer,

546
00:47:19,000 --> 00:47:20,870
but in place of this weak,
pathetic mother,

547
00:47:22,910 --> 00:47:23,940
you have Director Shin,
someone who cherishes you...

548
00:47:25,180 --> 00:47:27,510
and loves you so dearly.

549
00:47:28,580 --> 00:47:29,750
I can leave now, because I trust him.

550
00:47:32,580 --> 00:47:34,320
Please, let me go without any tears.

551
00:47:37,450 --> 00:47:38,460
I feel deeply sorry...

552
00:47:39,390 --> 00:47:41,660
to Dr. Jung,

553
00:47:42,160 --> 00:47:45,100
who tried everything...

554
00:47:45,930 --> 00:47:46,960
to cure the sickness in my soul.

555
00:47:49,030 --> 00:47:50,470
To my many acquaintances,

556
00:47:52,240 --> 00:47:54,540
I can see all their faces now.

557
00:47:56,740 --> 00:47:59,610
My dear daughter,
don't be foolish like me...

558
00:48:00,010 --> 00:48:02,180
and don't bury yourself in your work.

559
00:48:03,610 --> 00:48:07,580
From now on, learn to enjoy life a little,

560
00:48:08,890 --> 00:48:10,790
and always try to keep your spirits up.

561
00:48:15,290 --> 00:48:19,800
Please, live a long and healthy life.
Live well, for my sake too.

562
00:48:22,170 --> 00:48:25,040
The good deeds I wasn't able to finish...

563
00:48:26,870 --> 00:48:28,870
Do plenty of them with Director Shin.

564
00:48:30,810 --> 00:48:32,510
I don't want to be buried
in the cold, dark ground.

565
00:48:35,110 --> 00:48:36,110
Please have me cremated.

566
00:48:39,080 --> 00:48:41,320
I love you, my daughter.

567
00:48:44,120 --> 00:48:49,560
(Paul Kim)

568
00:48:54,000 --> 00:48:56,930
(Incoming Call)

569
00:49:01,100 --> 00:49:02,110
This is Paul Kim.

570
00:49:02,740 --> 00:49:07,010
Hi, I'm calling about the painting
you sold to CEO James Ha of Lim Company.

571
00:49:08,680 --> 00:49:09,680
Yes.

572
00:49:10,180 --> 00:49:11,650
I'm an acquaintance of CEO Ha's.

573
00:49:12,380 --> 00:49:15,090
I found the mood of that painting
so unique and refreshing.

574
00:49:15,890 --> 00:49:17,720
I assume you have other pieces
at your studio?

575
00:49:18,820 --> 00:49:22,530
- I do.
- I'd like to purchase one. May I stop by?

576
00:49:22,830 --> 00:49:24,630
My studio is on the outskirts of Seoul.

577
00:49:24,930 --> 00:49:27,200
That's fine.
It's only one hour at most with traffic.

578
00:49:27,600 --> 00:49:28,600
Do you have the address?

579
00:49:29,870 --> 00:49:30,970
Could you give it to me?

580
00:49:50,550 --> 00:49:51,620
It's open. Come on in.

581
00:50:10,940 --> 00:50:13,010
Paul Kim?

582
00:50:14,710 --> 00:50:15,710
Yes.

583
00:50:16,550 --> 00:50:18,720
Hello. Sorry I'm a bit late.

584
00:50:20,150 --> 00:50:23,390
The drive up here is just beautiful.

585
00:50:24,420 --> 00:50:25,420
Please, have a seat.

586
00:50:37,000 --> 00:50:39,170
You don't have any of your work
on display?

587
00:50:39,870 --> 00:50:40,870
No, I don't.

588
00:50:41,300 --> 00:50:42,770
They're in my studio
and on the second floor.

589
00:50:45,180 --> 00:50:47,410
- All I have is coffee.
- Coffee is perfect.

590
00:50:48,140 --> 00:50:49,680
No espresso, I presume?

591
00:50:52,920 --> 00:50:53,920
I'm just kidding.

592
00:50:59,160 --> 00:51:00,820
He surely is an artist.

593
00:51:01,660 --> 00:51:03,290
He's middle-aged,
but not an ounce of fat on him.

594
00:51:41,560 --> 00:51:42,570
This is delicious.

595
00:51:43,730 --> 00:51:44,730
It's German coffee.

596
00:51:45,470 --> 00:51:47,500
I heard you were based in Germany.

597
00:51:48,240 --> 00:51:49,240
Yes.

598
00:51:50,440 --> 00:51:53,480
I wasn't sure what to get you,
so I came empty-handed.

599
00:51:58,180 --> 00:51:59,180
You really didn't have to.

600
00:51:59,850 --> 00:52:00,850
There's nothing I need.

601
00:52:01,690 --> 00:52:02,820
I just meant some basic necessities.

602
00:52:04,920 --> 00:52:07,720
He's so stoic, like a Zen monk.

603
00:52:15,300 --> 00:52:16,300
I'm Hyun Ran Hee, by the way.

604
00:52:19,970 --> 00:52:21,670
(CEO Hyun Ran Hee)

605
00:52:23,940 --> 00:52:25,440
He must have heard of me.

606
00:52:28,210 --> 00:52:29,710
Do you do photography as well?

607
00:52:31,350 --> 00:52:32,350
Sometimes.

608
00:52:32,980 --> 00:52:34,620
So you must go out on photo shoots.

609
00:52:35,320 --> 00:52:37,020
When I have a block or feel drained.

610
00:52:37,620 --> 00:52:40,820
There's hardly any information
on you out there.

611
00:52:41,990 --> 00:52:43,490
When did you return to Korea?

612
00:52:44,460 --> 00:52:45,830
Seven months ago.

613
00:52:47,830 --> 00:52:50,700
So you knew CEO Ju before that?

614
00:52:51,300 --> 00:52:53,040
Yes, back in Germany.

615
00:52:54,740 --> 00:52:56,140
So CEO Ju sought you out?

616
00:52:56,610 --> 00:52:57,610
Yes.

617
00:52:57,940 --> 00:53:00,510
After seeing my work
at the Hong Kong Art Fair.

618
00:53:01,010 --> 00:53:02,780
The Hong Kong Art Fair? When was that?

619
00:53:03,410 --> 00:53:04,410
That was two years ago.

620
00:53:05,350 --> 00:53:08,150
I missed that one.

621
00:53:10,350 --> 00:53:11,960
No wedding ring, either.

622
00:53:26,240 --> 00:53:27,240
By any chance,

623
00:53:27,900 --> 00:53:30,070
is this a painting of someone
in your family?

624
00:53:31,370 --> 00:53:32,380
Your wife?

625
00:53:34,440 --> 00:53:36,550
It's just that the feeling
I get from it...

626
00:53:37,710 --> 00:53:38,780
is so profound.

627
00:53:40,680 --> 00:53:41,680
I don't have any family.

628
00:53:43,220 --> 00:53:45,620
Single? How attractive.

629
00:53:47,790 --> 00:53:50,890
When did you start focusing on people
as your subject?

630
00:53:52,430 --> 00:53:53,530
It's been a while.

631
00:53:54,660 --> 00:53:58,400
Clients love it.
These heartfelt paintings.

632
00:54:00,700 --> 00:54:02,040
This place is perfect for a studio.

633
00:54:02,640 --> 00:54:04,270
So, are you back for good?

634
00:54:05,080 --> 00:54:06,080
I am.

635
00:54:06,340 --> 00:54:09,450
Why don't I plan a solo exhibition
for you?

636
00:54:10,510 --> 00:54:11,610
Is it because of CEO Ju?

637
00:54:13,250 --> 00:54:14,450
Mother's Gallery?

638
00:54:15,250 --> 00:54:16,250
We're in talks.

639
00:54:18,190 --> 00:54:20,320
I'll take this with me today.

640
00:54:22,190 --> 00:54:23,430
She hasn't changed a bit.

641
00:54:32,870 --> 00:54:34,970
(Paul Kim)

642
00:54:41,410 --> 00:54:42,510
(Paul Kim)

643
00:54:42,650 --> 00:54:43,680
If you find her,

644
00:54:44,410 --> 00:54:46,480
tell her...

645
00:54:47,080 --> 00:54:48,080
that her mom was so, so sorry.

646
00:54:48,890 --> 00:54:51,250
You have to find her. No matter what.

647
00:55:38,540 --> 00:55:39,740
(One Missed Call, Ran Hee)

648
00:55:43,840 --> 00:55:44,910
If you find her,

649
00:55:45,580 --> 00:55:47,810
tell her...

650
00:55:48,310 --> 00:55:49,310
that her mom was so, so sorry.

651
00:55:50,110 --> 00:55:52,520
You have to find her. No matter what.

652
00:55:52,650 --> 00:55:54,750
(Ran Hee)

653
00:55:57,920 --> 00:56:01,690
The person you have called is unavailable.
Please leave a message after the tone.

654
00:56:09,070 --> 00:56:10,100
Hyun Ran Hee.

655
00:56:10,870 --> 00:56:12,300
You've worked so hard.

656
00:56:15,540 --> 00:56:16,910
And you're still so young.

657
00:56:17,640 --> 00:56:19,110
Still in your prime.

658
00:56:21,010 --> 00:56:22,480
That girl just wouldn't listen.

659
00:56:23,180 --> 00:56:25,280
I warned her over and over
that it was dangerous.

660
00:56:25,980 --> 00:56:26,980
Is this my karma?

661
00:56:28,280 --> 00:56:29,720
Even if it is, it can't be helped.

662
00:58:36,950 --> 00:58:38,410
Hello, is this the Immigration Office?

663
00:58:39,020 --> 00:58:41,850
I'm calling to check if an acquaintance
of mine has left the country.

664
00:58:41,920 --> 00:58:43,950
I can't let you know
as it's personal information.

665
00:58:43,950 --> 00:58:45,490
Not even if I come to the office?

666
00:58:45,590 --> 00:58:46,590
It wouldn't make a difference.

667
00:58:47,990 --> 00:58:48,990
I see.

668
00:58:55,470 --> 00:58:56,900
It's 911. What's your emergency?

669
00:58:57,300 --> 00:59:00,640
- I...
- Please state your emergency.

670
00:59:00,940 --> 00:59:04,310
Hurry. Please come quick. It's my mom...

671
00:59:04,740 --> 00:59:08,510
We had a few calls.
Mr. Oh Young Sik woke up in distress.

672
00:59:08,640 --> 00:59:11,680
He's intubated,
so he couldn't express himself clearly.

673
00:59:11,910 --> 00:59:16,220
Remifentanil didn't work.
So we used Propofol, and he settled down.

674
00:59:16,550 --> 00:59:20,860
When we started Precedex for sedation,
his blood pressure dropped slightly...

675
00:59:21,190 --> 00:59:23,560
(Conference Room)

676
00:59:23,730 --> 00:59:24,730
Hello?

677
00:59:27,130 --> 00:59:32,000
(Nua General Hospital ICU gets top rating
in quality assessment!)

678
00:59:32,370 --> 00:59:36,870
We can run a check,
but it's logged in the immigration system.

679
00:59:37,610 --> 00:59:38,610
Who is it?

680
00:59:39,810 --> 00:59:41,680
- A celebrity.
- Which one?

681
00:59:42,380 --> 00:59:44,910
I'll tell you,
but you have to stick your neck out.

682
00:59:44,980 --> 00:59:47,220
If I stick my neck out and lose my job,
are you going to take responsibility?

683
00:59:47,280 --> 00:59:50,750
- You won't be fired for this.
- Get forensics to Momo's house, now!

684
00:59:53,520 --> 00:59:56,330
What's going on at Momo's?
What happened? An accident?

685
00:59:57,990 --> 01:00:00,130
Don't you know me?
You're the one who called me a pit bull.

686
01:00:02,270 --> 01:00:04,400
It looks like Momo's mother
committed suicide.

687
01:00:04,830 --> 01:00:05,970
We still have to investigate, though.

688
01:00:06,340 --> 01:00:08,270
- Why?
- How would I know?

689
01:00:08,910 --> 01:00:09,910
What about Momo?

690
01:00:10,410 --> 01:00:11,970
Apparently, she's the one who called 911.

691
01:00:13,680 --> 01:00:14,880
(Forensics)

692
01:00:19,420 --> 01:00:21,150
(Sungwoo Daily)

693
01:00:25,120 --> 01:00:26,120
(Headline)

694
01:00:26,190 --> 01:00:27,790
("Hyun Gallery CEO Hyun Ran Hee
Found Dead")

695
01:00:29,330 --> 01:00:30,460
("Hyun Gallery CEO Hyun Ran Hee
Found Dead")

696
01:00:30,460 --> 01:00:31,560
("Momo Called 911")

697
01:00:32,530 --> 01:00:34,800
(Reporter Geum Ba Ra)

698
01:00:35,000 --> 01:00:36,900
("Hyun Gallery CEO Hyun Ran Hee
Found Dead")

699
01:00:40,200 --> 01:00:42,470
(Momo discovered the body and called 911.)

700
01:00:42,540 --> 01:00:44,640
(Reporter Geum Ba Ra)

701
01:00:46,910 --> 01:00:48,740
(Reporter Geum Ba Ra)

702
01:01:15,770 --> 01:01:18,610
(Doctor Shin)

703
01:01:18,740 --> 01:01:20,410
No way. This can't be happening. How?

704
01:01:20,980 --> 01:01:23,450
- What is it, sir?
- She's relentless.

705
01:01:25,410 --> 01:01:26,420
Momo...

706
01:01:28,120 --> 01:01:30,020
James, doesn't your company sponsor Momo?

707
01:01:30,720 --> 01:01:32,290
- Yes.
- Can you introduce me?

708
01:01:32,360 --> 01:01:35,360
I didn't realize you were his best friend.
I made a complete fool of myself.

709
01:01:35,420 --> 01:01:37,460
- I'm Ha Yong Joong.
- I'm Momo.

710
01:01:37,530 --> 01:01:40,760
I can't believe it.
She got all that work done on her face,

711
01:01:40,900 --> 01:01:43,870
- and she looked so happy.
- Hyun Ran Hee is the one who died.

712
01:01:44,370 --> 01:01:45,970
Things are not what they seem.

713
01:01:46,600 --> 01:01:50,210
Just take it for what it is.
No need to overthink it.

714
01:01:50,770 --> 01:01:51,810
Loosen your tie before you go.

715
01:01:52,340 --> 01:01:55,750
I wonder where my daughter is
and if she's growing up well.

716
01:01:56,180 --> 01:01:59,850
He was the one who saw the good in me
when I felt worthless.

717
01:02:00,580 --> 01:02:03,990
- Yong Joong.
- They didn't even do CPR.

